from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
from matplotlib import cm

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

step = 0.1
x = np.arange(-5, 5 + step, step)
y = np.arange(-5, 5 + step, step)
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(x, y)
sigma = 1
g = np.exp(-(xx**2 + yy**2)/(2*sigma**2))

surf = ax.plot_surface(xx, yy, g, cmap=cm.jet)
cset = ax.contourf(xx, yy, g, zdir='z', offset=np.min(g) - 1.5, cmap=cm.jet)
ax.set_zlim(np.min(g) -2, np.max(g))

plt.axis('off')

plt.show()

f_h = cv.filter2D(im, -1, sobel_h)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 16))

axes[2].set_title("Sobel horizontal")
axes[2].axis('off')

im = cv.imread(r"D:\Academics\Semester 4\Machine Vision\Homeworks\Documents\Homework3\tom.jpg", cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE).astype(np.float32)
assert im is not None

gaussian_1d = cv.getGaussianKernel(5, 2)
im_lp = cv.sepFilter2D(im, -1, gaussian_1d, gaussian_1d)
im_hp = im - im_lp
im_sharp = cv.addWeighted(im, 1.0, im_hp, 2.0, 0)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize = (18,6)) 
axes[0].imshow(im, cmap = 'gray')
axes[0].set_title('original')
axes[0].axis('off')

axes[1].imshow(im_lp, cmap = 'gray')
axes[1].set_title('f_lp')
axes[1].axis('off')

axes[2].imshow(im_hp, cmap = 'gray')
axes[2].set_title('f_hp')
axes[2].axis('off')

axes[3].imshow(im_sharp, cmap = 'gray')
axes[3].set_title('Sharpened')
axes[3].axis('off')

plt.show()
